trans-unit.source: Boolean value that specifies whether to suppress the GDI+ background thread.

target.mrk: Boolean value that specifies whether to suppress the GDI+ background thread.

trans-unit.source: If you set this member to True, GdiplusStartup returns a pointer to a hook function and a pointer to an unhook function.

seg-source.mrk: If you set this member to True, GdiplusStartup returns a pointer to a hook function and a pointer to an unhook function.

target.mrk: If you set this member to True, GdiplusStartup returns a pointer to a hook function and a pointer to an unhook function.

trans-unit.source: You must call those functions appropriately to replace the background thread.

seg-source.mrk: You must call those functions appropriately to replace the background thread.

target.mrk: You must call those functions appropriately to replace the background thread.

trans-unit.source: If you do not want to be responsible for calling the hook and unhook functions, set this member to False.
